<br>
I don&#39;t hope to see this deck in top 10, I just wanna improve it, it&#39;s already quite good, but I belive can be better, please help me improve it.<br>
<br>
Cards explanation and some tips:<br>
-Generally, bid 3 go first<br>
-Gandalf is killing machine, he can be 12 power, which is very nice<br>
-Pippin, Mr. Took- deploy Gandalf, Aragorn, and let Cave Troll kill him<br>
-Gimli, Dwarf of the Mountain Race- first of all, I live him very much; also in big fellowship with his axe vs. moria can be very useful- drop the weakest orc against and kill the other with axe<br>
-Sam, Proper Poet- Broken card; I usually drop him at site 6 or 7; make him defender +1 and let him die<br>
-Thrarin- same as Sam, try not to kill him before site  9<br>
-Hobbit Stealth- only one, but it&#39;s enough; Frodo usually don&#39;t face to many minions; good with fierce minions and Pippin (Cave Troll- Pippin stealth, fierce Pippin dies, whatever?)<br>
-O Elbereth! Glithoniel- I like this card, good against Witch-King or other powerful Nazgul<br>
-Troop of Uruk-Hai- He will win skirmish always; I like them better than Lurtz, Lurtz is too expensive<br>
-Uruk-Hai Raiding Party- 3 vitality for 4, IMHO good deal; also Greenleaf can&#39;t kill him <br>
-Tower Asassin- I hate Elrond, Bounders, he can easily kill them; very useful in every Uruk-hai deck<br>
-Saruman&#39;s Power- kill Promises, The Last Alliance of Elves and Men, Tale of Gil-Galad, Saga of Elendil, and much more<br>
-Ettenmoors + Troop of Uruk-Hai +Saruman&#39;s Ambition/Savagery means dead companion on site 2<br>
